Synopsis:
   set status_server [<text>]

Description:
   This variable contains the string displayed in the status bar when the
   client is connected to a server in the current window.  If the client
   is not connect to a server in the current window, nothing is shown.

   This string is represented by %S in the STATUS_SERVER string.  If the
   expando is used inside STATUS_SERVER, it expands to the server name.

Examples:
   Customizing the current server indicator:
      /set status_server Server: %S

See Also:
   set(4) status_format; server(1)

